1
00:00:58,259 --> 00:01:02,807
[Episode 7: Low-Power Mode Human]

2
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:46,715
- Spin it, spin it!
- Come on, faster!

3
00:01:46,715 --> 00:01:50,292
<i>People fall into two types.</i>

4
00:01:50,292 --> 00:01:55,080
<i>Some get energized being around people...</i>

5
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:58,750
<i>Others get totally drained in crowds.</i>

6
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:00,377
<i>That's me.</i>

7
00:02:00,377 --> 00:02:03,380
See? Told you he could do it.

8
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:05,485
Did you see his speed?

9
00:02:05,485 --> 00:02:06,758
Yeah, I saw it.

10
00:02:06,758 --> 00:02:08,702
- Pretty insane, right?
- Seriously.

11
00:02:08,702 --> 00:02:11,213
That was incredible.

12
00:02:12,113 --> 00:02:14,332
Let's get a hit!

13
00:02:15,934 --> 00:02:17,603
- Get up, PD Shin.
- No, I'm good.

14
00:02:17,603 --> 00:02:18,896
Come on, get up. Join us.

15
00:02:18,896 --> 00:02:21,356
Let me hear you!

16
00:02:21,356 --> 00:02:23,759
<i>♪ Get a hit, come on ♪</i>

17
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:26,445
<i>♪ Get a hit ♪</i>
Go, go!

18
00:02:26,445 --> 00:02:28,071
<i>♪ We want a home run ♪</i>

19
00:02:28,071 --> 00:02:31,074
How?
<i>♪ Knock it out of the park ♪</i>

20
00:02:31,074 --> 00:02:32,868
<i>♪ Send it flying ♪</i>
Get a hit!

21
00:02:32,868 --> 00:02:35,496
<i>♪ Get a hit, come on ♪</i>

22
00:02:35,496 --> 00:02:38,040
<i>♪ Get a hit ♪</i>

23
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:40,375
<i>♪ We want a home run ♪</i>
Sorry, my boss is calling.

24
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:42,794
How?
<i>♪ Knock it out of the park ♪</i>

25
00:02:42,794 --> 00:02:47,298
<i>♪ Send it flying, right now ♪</i>

26
00:02:51,386 --> 00:02:53,542
Okay, got it.

27
00:02:53,542 --> 00:02:56,600
I'll double-check and send it over.

28
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,319
Okay.

29
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:06,235
<i>If I weren't managing a writer
who writes baseball novels,</i>

30
00:03:06,235 --> 00:03:08,953
<i>I'd never be somewhere like this.</i>

31
00:03:27,965 --> 00:03:30,450
<i>To conserve energy,</i>

32
00:03:30,450 --> 00:03:33,877
<i>I stay in low-power mode outside.</i>

33
00:03:38,517 --> 00:03:40,435
<i>So during the day,</i>

34
00:03:40,435 --> 00:03:43,863
<i>only Rational Cell is active.</i>

35
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,900
Look at that.

36
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,570
When did all those flowers bloom?

37
00:03:49,570 --> 00:03:50,612
Yeah.

38
00:03:50,612 --> 00:03:53,615
The weather's so nice today.

39
00:03:53,615 --> 00:03:55,576
I want to go out.

40
00:03:55,576 --> 00:03:57,452
Same here.

41
00:03:57,452 --> 00:03:59,813
Should we just ditch work right now?

42
00:03:59,813 --> 00:04:02,103
- Really?
- Really?

43
00:04:03,362 --> 00:04:06,417
No way. Absolutely not.

44
00:04:07,143 --> 00:04:09,028
Too bad.

45
00:04:17,586 --> 00:04:20,483
<i>The Rational Cell doesn't get caught up
in pointless emotions.</i>

46
00:04:20,483 --> 00:04:22,477
<i>That's why it works fast.</i>

47
00:04:22,477 --> 00:04:24,062
<i>Plus...</i>

48
00:04:24,062 --> 00:04:26,022
Would you like something to drink?

49
00:04:26,022 --> 00:04:28,574
No, I'm good.

50
00:04:29,943 --> 00:04:32,292
Oh, I have some chocolates I got as a gift...

51
00:04:32,292 --> 00:04:33,863
Then...

52
00:04:33,863 --> 00:04:36,875
I should get going.

53
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:37,934
Okay.

54
00:04:37,934 --> 00:04:40,237
<i>I'm good at saying no, too.</i>

55
00:04:45,475 --> 00:04:48,316
<i>Keeping clear boundaries
also helps me save energy.</i>

56
00:04:48,316 --> 00:04:51,236
You're really calm and rational.

57
00:04:51,236 --> 00:04:53,098
Nice.

58
00:04:58,583 --> 00:04:59,914
<i>Calm and rational.</i>

59
00:04:59,914 --> 00:05:03,341
<i>That's how people see Soon Rok.</i>

60
00:05:05,395 --> 00:05:08,729
Strike three!

61
00:05:08,729 --> 00:05:10,542
- Strike three!
- Editor.

62
00:05:10,542 --> 00:05:12,110
Here, sir.

63
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:15,071
Strike three!

64
00:05:15,071 --> 00:05:16,983
Strike three!

65
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,491
Strike three!

66
00:05:18,491 --> 00:05:20,092
Come on, do better than that.

67
00:05:20,092 --> 00:05:21,703
Strike three!

68
00:05:21,703 --> 00:05:23,605
<i>The only downside is,</i>

69
00:05:23,605 --> 00:05:24,947
<i>when he's outside,</i>

70
00:05:24,947 --> 00:05:28,791
<i>none of his other cells are active.</i>

71
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:31,660
Let's dig in.

72
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:34,089
Oh, thanks.

73
00:05:34,089 --> 00:05:36,500
That marinated crab looks incredible.

74
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,176
- I'm already drooling.
- Eat up.

75
00:05:38,176 --> 00:05:40,875
Not my treat though.

76
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:43,096
Enjoy. Food's all that matters anyway.

77
00:05:43,096 --> 00:05:44,887
What else is there in life?

78
00:05:46,226 --> 00:05:48,620
<i>I don't even register what I'm eating.</i>

79
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:51,564
Hey, "Attack of the Bats" just came out.

80
00:05:51,564 --> 00:05:52,792
Who's in after this?

81
00:05:52,792 --> 00:05:54,692
- Me! I've been wanting to see it!
- Of course.

82
00:05:54,692 --> 00:05:57,628
Let's go, go!

83
00:05:57,628 --> 00:05:59,739
Sorry, but I...

84
00:05:59,739 --> 00:06:02,208
You're coming, right, PD Shin?

85
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,453
If you're not going, I'm not going either.

86
00:06:04,453 --> 00:06:05,495
I mean it.

87
00:06:05,495 --> 00:06:07,330
- Come on, PD Shin.
- Come on.

88
00:06:07,330 --> 00:06:08,542
I'm not going either.

89
00:06:08,542 --> 00:06:10,083
- Come with us.
- PD Shin!

90
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:12,710
- You have to come.
- PD Shin!

91
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:15,304
PD Shin!

92
00:06:40,113 --> 00:06:42,790
He's spilling the popcorn.

93
00:07:04,861 --> 00:07:08,298
Who checks their phone in a theater?

94
00:07:16,415 --> 00:07:19,944
<i>I can't even focus on the movie.</i>

95
00:07:19,944 --> 00:07:21,846
Isn't it getting pretty late?

96
00:07:21,846 --> 00:07:23,615
There it is.

97
00:07:23,615 --> 00:07:26,333
The movie was longer than expected.

98
00:07:27,302 --> 00:07:28,575
I'll get going.

99
00:07:28,575 --> 00:07:29,633
Bye.

100
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:31,208
Get home safe.

101
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:34,008
Don't say you were with us.

102
00:07:41,765 --> 00:07:43,009
Hello.

103
00:07:43,009 --> 00:07:46,949
<i>On top of that, I'm running out of time.</i>

104
00:07:50,263 --> 00:07:53,076
<i>The door's closing.</i>

105
00:08:00,482 --> 00:08:01,908
<i>Hello.</i>

106
00:08:01,908 --> 00:08:03,321
<i>I'm still not comfortable with this team.</i>

107
00:08:03,321 --> 00:08:05,434
<i>Sorry, I'm a bit late...</i>

108
00:08:05,434 --> 00:08:09,227
<i>And now there's even a dog.</i>

109
00:08:13,081 --> 00:08:15,083
PD Shin,

110
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:17,760
do you have anything to say?

111
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:27,637
<i>Gosh.</i>

112
00:08:27,637 --> 00:08:30,717
<i>I can't focus on the script.</i>

113
00:08:31,599 --> 00:08:33,685
<i>"How can someone in love"</i>

114
00:08:33,685 --> 00:08:36,362
<i>"possibly stay calm?"</i>

115
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:42,277
Sorry, what does that even mean?

116
00:08:42,277 --> 00:08:46,538
"How can someone in love possibly stay calm?"

117
00:08:47,740 --> 00:08:51,025
What does love have to do with being calm?

118
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,167
<i>A Maltese.</i>

119
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:03,487
<i>Yeah, let's just talk about the Maltese.</i>

120
00:09:03,487 --> 00:09:06,676
<i>No need to overthink that one.</i>

121
00:09:06,676 --> 00:09:08,382
But Maltese dogs

122
00:09:08,382 --> 00:09:10,305
aren't that smart.

123
00:09:10,305 --> 00:09:11,948
They're not?

124
00:09:11,948 --> 00:09:13,250
I thought they were.

125
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:15,001
Not particularly.

126
00:09:15,001 --> 00:09:16,644
That's it.

127
00:09:16,644 --> 00:09:18,296
Nice save, Soon Rok.

128
00:09:18,296 --> 00:09:21,515
Let's dodge the situation with the Maltese.

129
00:09:23,376 --> 00:09:26,678
When I'm in a bad mood,
she stays quiet beside me...

130
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,034
She's actually really smart.

131
00:09:31,034 --> 00:09:33,339
Don't all dogs do that?

132
00:09:33,339 --> 00:09:35,500
Unless it's a lizard.

133
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,708
Right.

134
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:40,862
Dogs and lizards.
That's an interesting comparison.

135
00:09:51,596 --> 00:09:53,289
<i>Going down.</i>

136
00:09:53,289 --> 00:09:54,467
Good work today.

137
00:09:54,467 --> 00:09:55,588
Good work.

138
00:09:55,588 --> 00:09:58,179
Hang in there.

139
00:09:58,179 --> 00:10:00,088
- Bye, Coco.
- Take care.

140
00:10:00,088 --> 00:10:02,515
<i>The door's closing.</i>

141
00:10:06,957 --> 00:10:08,042
But...

142
00:10:08,042 --> 00:10:10,333
Writer Kim should be a little upset.

143
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,392
Why?

144
00:10:11,392 --> 00:10:14,324
You know, PD Shin said
Maltese dogs aren't that smart.

145
00:10:14,324 --> 00:10:16,111
Yeah, she didn't seem too happy.

146
00:10:16,111 --> 00:10:17,913
I wasn't talking about her.

147
00:10:17,913 --> 00:10:20,482
I said the Maltese wasn't smart.
Why would she be upset?

148
00:10:20,482 --> 00:10:22,250
Still, from her perspective...

149
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:24,188
It's not even her dog.

150
00:10:24,188 --> 00:10:27,356
Even so, it just feels...

151
00:10:27,356 --> 00:10:29,216
Oh my, you're so cold.

152
00:10:29,216 --> 00:10:31,517
Way too rational.

153
00:10:34,221 --> 00:10:35,889
What are they talking about?

154
00:10:35,889 --> 00:10:38,642
Writer Kim isn't a Maltese,

155
00:10:38,642 --> 00:10:40,673
and she's not even the owner.

156
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:44,046
So why would she be upset?

157
00:10:45,774 --> 00:10:48,843
I don't know.

158
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:11,550
Today was too much.

159
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:15,760
I carried the whole day on my own.

160
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,098
<i>I know.</i>

161
00:11:18,098 --> 00:11:19,917
<i>But it's okay.</i>

162
00:11:19,917 --> 00:11:21,978
<i>I'm almost home.</i>

163
00:12:19,450 --> 00:12:21,625
<i>Because I'm...</i>

164
00:12:23,746 --> 00:12:26,172
<i>a total homebody.</i>

165
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,476
Going out is exhausting.

166
00:12:45,476 --> 00:12:48,111
Home is the best.

167
00:12:54,276 --> 00:12:57,579
<i>When I'm home, all my senses come alive.</i>

168
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:12,519
Perfect.

169
00:13:16,006 --> 00:13:18,058
<i>My sense of taste kicks in,</i>

170
00:13:20,511 --> 00:13:22,604
<i>and my hearing sharpens,</i>

171
00:13:38,028 --> 00:13:39,375
That's it!

172
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:41,490
Good eye!

173
00:13:41,490 --> 00:13:43,556
Bases loaded!

174
00:13:44,243 --> 00:13:46,309
Yes!

175
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:50,875
<i>Baseball is best with commentary.</i>

176
00:14:04,542 --> 00:14:06,593
Is he dead?

177
00:14:18,818 --> 00:14:21,324
<i>Movies are meant to be watched
from the comfort of home.</i>

178
00:14:21,324 --> 00:14:23,198
<i>That's the way to do it.</i>

179
00:14:26,993 --> 00:14:30,063
<i>At home, my emotions peak,</i>

180
00:14:30,063 --> 00:14:32,299
<i>and I can even pick up
on the writer's hidden intentions</i>

181
00:14:32,299 --> 00:14:34,375
<i>between the lines.</i>

182
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:35,585
<i>Back then...</i>

183
00:14:35,585 --> 00:14:37,212
<i>Did he leave his phone behind?</i>

184
00:14:37,212 --> 00:14:39,881
<i>The phone began to ring,</i>

185
00:14:39,881 --> 00:14:43,551
<i>and Sun Ju's eyes were drawn to it.</i>

186
00:14:43,551 --> 00:14:46,262
<i>Whose call could it be?</i>

187
00:14:46,262 --> 00:14:48,389
<i>A name she had forgotten.</i>

188
00:14:48,389 --> 00:14:50,304
[Yoo Da Eun, Intern]
<i>It was Eun Young.</i>

189
00:14:51,351 --> 00:14:54,812
<i>In that moment, Sun Ju realized</i>

190
00:14:54,812 --> 00:14:58,183
<i>just how calm she was.</i>

191
00:14:58,183 --> 00:15:01,950
[Missed Call]

192
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:30,598
<i>How can someone in love</i>

193
00:15:30,598 --> 00:15:33,482
<i>possibly stay calm?</i>

194
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,840
It wasn't about the Maltese...

195
00:15:47,623 --> 00:15:50,159
<i>Writer Kim, this is Shin Soon Rok.</i>

196
00:15:50,159 --> 00:15:53,158
<i>I've added my feedback and sent it over.</i>

197
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:14,240
<i>A homebody's nights are always too short.</i>

198
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:20,784
<i>And the worst thing for someone like me is...</i>

199
00:16:25,881 --> 00:16:27,387
[PD Jang Su Hye]

200
00:16:28,551 --> 00:16:30,167
- Hello?
<i>- Hey, Soon Rok.</i>

201
00:16:30,167 --> 00:16:31,868
Sorry, are you home right now?

202
00:16:31,868 --> 00:16:33,647
Do you have anything going on today?

203
00:16:33,647 --> 00:16:35,371
No.

204
00:16:35,371 --> 00:16:37,147
But why...

205
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:42,064
Right now?

206
00:16:42,931 --> 00:16:44,645
<i>A day like this.</i>

207
00:16:45,716 --> 00:16:48,220
<i>An unplanned... weekend business trip.</i>

208
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:50,289
Okay, I understand.

209
00:16:50,289 --> 00:16:53,567
What the...

210
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:56,077
It's Saturday.

211
00:17:20,530 --> 00:17:24,043
<i>There's no time. Just go.</i>

212
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,944
Hello.

213
00:17:54,495 --> 00:17:56,700
[From Seoul to Busan]

214
00:18:02,029 --> 00:18:04,352
I forgot my glasses.

215
00:18:04,352 --> 00:18:07,103
<i>You even forgot your glasses?</i>

216
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:12,133
Wait, no.

217
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:14,464
If I burn out this early,

218
00:18:14,464 --> 00:18:17,195
how am I supposed to get through today?

219
00:18:34,081 --> 00:18:35,882
Sorry.

220
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:07,355
You're really going to
meet the writer like this?

221
00:19:07,355 --> 00:19:10,274
You didn't even wash your face.

222
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:12,355
What about your image?

223
00:19:24,546 --> 00:19:25,750
That's good.

224
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:28,084
I didn't want to go alone anyway.

225
00:19:28,084 --> 00:19:30,167
Please, have a seat.

226
00:19:30,167 --> 00:19:32,004
<i>Sit far away.</i>

227
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,089
No, it's okay.

228
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:35,135
My seat is over there.

229
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:52,525
You don't even know the schedule yet.

230
00:19:52,525 --> 00:19:56,028
You're a mess, and you forgot your glasses.

231
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:59,338
Gosh, today is seriously the worst.

232
00:19:59,338 --> 00:20:02,118
Yes, I received the book talk materials,

233
00:20:02,118 --> 00:20:05,896
but I don't have the contact info
for the person in charge.

234
00:20:05,896 --> 00:20:07,875
Yes, thank you.

235
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:10,251
Oh, sorry, and also...

236
00:20:10,251 --> 00:20:11,795
the car...

237
00:20:11,795 --> 00:20:13,624
Oh, the rental.

238
00:20:13,624 --> 00:20:15,038
Yes.

239
00:20:21,097 --> 00:20:23,389
Let me sit here for a moment.

240
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:24,515
<i>What?</i>

241
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:27,199
<i>What is she saying?</i>

242
00:20:27,199 --> 00:20:29,228
I need to tell you something.

243
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:32,028
Do you not like working with me?

244
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:35,845
What?

245
00:20:38,279 --> 00:20:40,375
What did she just say?

246
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:44,035
She asked if he doesn't like working with her?

247
00:20:44,035 --> 00:20:45,620
<i>I don't know either.</i>

248
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:46,875
<i>I'm not sure what she means.</i>

249
00:20:46,875 --> 00:20:48,998
Could you explain more specifically?

250
00:20:48,998 --> 00:20:51,165
I think I need to hear this.

251
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:58,631
What does she want to hear?

252
00:20:58,631 --> 00:21:00,342
Specifically?

253
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,625
What is she talking about?

254
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:04,958
Is she mad right now?

255
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:06,500
Why is she mad?

256
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:09,100
She even brought me a drink earlier.

257
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:10,768
What is this all of a sudden?

258
00:21:10,768 --> 00:21:13,421
No...

259
00:21:14,897 --> 00:21:16,251
Yeah?

260
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:19,402
I'm not sure what you mean...

261
00:21:19,402 --> 00:21:22,167
I mean I want to know the real reason.

262
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:24,309
Why you're leaving our team.

263
00:21:24,309 --> 00:21:26,750
Didn't the Editor tell you?

264
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:28,035
My schedules kept overlapping...

265
00:21:28,035 --> 00:21:30,016
That's just an excuse.

266
00:21:30,016 --> 00:21:31,826
An excuse?

267
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:33,875
PD Shin.

268
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:36,373
I've been patient for a long time.

269
00:21:36,373 --> 00:21:39,285
I'm not usually someone
who gets this worked up,

270
00:21:39,285 --> 00:21:42,485
but lately, it's been really frustrating.

271
00:21:46,443 --> 00:21:47,472
What?

272
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:50,218
Something's seriously off here.

273
00:21:52,059 --> 00:21:54,295
Everyone, wake up!

274
00:21:54,295 --> 00:21:57,581
This is an emergency!

275
00:22:01,584 --> 00:22:03,501
No!

276
00:22:05,156 --> 00:22:06,429
<i>My gosh.</i>

277
00:22:06,429 --> 00:22:09,785
<i>He's completely drained.</i>

278
00:22:09,785 --> 00:22:11,595
PD Shin?

279
00:22:35,708 --> 00:22:38,903
[Episode 8: Out of the Blue]

280
00:22:50,618 --> 00:22:52,411
PD Shin?

281
00:23:10,319 --> 00:23:11,889
Is he smiling?

282
00:23:11,889 --> 00:23:14,058
He's smiling right now?

283
00:23:14,058 --> 00:23:15,083
Why is he smiling?

284
00:23:15,083 --> 00:23:16,441
Yumi's serious now.

285
00:23:16,441 --> 00:23:17,645
Are you kidding?

286
00:23:17,645 --> 00:23:20,705
You should answer her.
What the hell are you laughing for?

287
00:23:24,125 --> 00:23:27,446
Yumi just laid everything out there,

288
00:23:29,046 --> 00:23:32,528
so why aren't you saying anything? You punk!

289
00:23:33,825 --> 00:23:37,347
What was that? There weren't even any clouds.

290
00:24:00,452 --> 00:24:02,126
Hey...

291
00:24:03,115 --> 00:24:04,266
PD Shin,

292
00:24:04,266 --> 00:24:06,818
why were you smiling...

293
00:24:08,134 --> 00:24:09,848
[PD Jang Su Hye]

294
00:24:11,657 --> 00:24:14,807
Sorry, this is an urgent call.

295
00:24:18,873 --> 00:24:20,458
Hello?

296
00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:22,041
Yes.

297
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:25,321
We'll arrive in about an hour.

298
00:24:25,321 --> 00:24:29,382
No, I think we should stop by the hotel first.

299
00:24:29,382 --> 00:24:31,801
And also...

300
00:24:31,801 --> 00:24:33,282
Sorry?

301
00:24:38,417 --> 00:24:43,208
<i>This stop is Singyeongju. Singyeongju Station.</i>

302
00:24:43,208 --> 00:24:46,066
<i>Please make sure to exit
after the train comes to a complete stop.</i>

303
00:24:46,066 --> 00:24:49,319
Has the schedule been shared
with the Editor as well?

304
00:24:49,319 --> 00:24:51,279
As far as I know,

305
00:24:51,279 --> 00:24:54,824
he's on the noon train.

306
00:24:54,824 --> 00:24:56,560
Okay, then...

307
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:59,120
I'll double-check and get back to you.

308
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,837
- Yes, thank you.
<i>- Doors are opening.</i>

309
00:25:05,022 --> 00:25:07,087
Hello.

310
00:25:07,087 --> 00:25:09,548
About tomorrow's event...

311
00:25:09,548 --> 00:25:10,799
Yes.

312
00:25:10,799 --> 00:25:13,009
Right.

313
00:25:13,009 --> 00:25:16,417
I heard briefly, but what kind of video...

314
00:25:25,730 --> 00:25:27,550
What?

315
00:25:36,199 --> 00:25:38,595
What is he even doing?

316
00:25:42,318 --> 00:25:44,457
What was that just now?

317
00:25:44,457 --> 00:25:45,542
I don't know.

318
00:25:45,542 --> 00:25:48,125
Where did that come from all of a sudden?

319
00:25:48,125 --> 00:25:49,282
Guys...

320
00:25:49,282 --> 00:25:50,792
I have a bad feeling.

321
00:25:50,792 --> 00:25:52,125
What if...

322
00:25:52,125 --> 00:25:55,000
it's the Hysterical Cell?

323
00:25:59,347 --> 00:26:02,365
But the Hysterical Cell is
in the freezer facility.

324
00:26:02,365 --> 00:26:04,893
What if it woke up

325
00:26:04,893 --> 00:26:06,625
because of Soon Rok?

326
00:26:06,625 --> 00:26:08,465
That's it.

327
00:26:08,465 --> 00:26:11,925
The Hysterical Cell woke up.

328
00:26:11,925 --> 00:26:13,592
Let's go.

329
00:26:18,074 --> 00:26:21,250
He just smiled and walked off to take a call.

330
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:23,333
What kind of crap is he pulling?

331
00:26:23,333 --> 00:26:25,290
That won't work on me.

332
00:26:25,290 --> 00:26:27,525
I'm hearing everything out
before I let this go.

333
00:26:27,525 --> 00:26:30,741
<i>- Doors are closing.</i>
- What time should I send it by?

334
00:26:30,741 --> 00:26:32,584
Okay, okay.

335
00:26:35,133 --> 00:26:37,738
<i>The train is departing.</i>

336
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,812
Hey!

337
00:26:47,812 --> 00:26:49,506
I see.

338
00:26:49,506 --> 00:26:51,316
- If you send the video...
- Hey!

339
00:26:51,316 --> 00:26:53,674
- I'll review it and decide...
- Hey!

340
00:26:53,674 --> 00:26:55,695
Yes, thank you.

341
00:26:55,695 --> 00:26:56,958
Okay, got it.

342
00:26:56,958 --> 00:26:59,714
- Hey!
- All right.

343
00:26:59,714 --> 00:27:01,348
Hey!

344
00:27:06,289 --> 00:27:08,487
Oh, come on...

345
00:27:08,487 --> 00:27:10,776
Writer Kim!

346
00:27:10,776 --> 00:27:12,837
Writer...

347
00:27:12,837 --> 00:27:14,680
Oh no.

348
00:27:20,890 --> 00:27:22,097
What the...

349
00:27:22,097 --> 00:27:23,890
Did he just miss the train?

350
00:27:23,890 --> 00:27:26,770
We're screwed. Totally screwed.

351
00:27:37,117 --> 00:27:39,044
What the...

352
00:27:39,044 --> 00:27:41,137
Seriously...

353
00:27:43,002 --> 00:27:44,987
Did he seriously miss the train?

354
00:27:44,987 --> 00:27:46,333
Unbelievable.

355
00:27:46,333 --> 00:27:47,907
Did he do that on purpose?

356
00:27:47,907 --> 00:27:49,167
Just to avoid talking to her?

357
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:50,208
Hey!

358
00:27:50,208 --> 00:27:53,375
You little bastard...

359
00:27:58,731 --> 00:28:00,133
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

360
00:28:00,133 --> 00:28:02,677
<i>I missed the train while on a call.</i>

361
00:28:02,677 --> 00:28:05,013
<i>I'll take the next train and catch up.</i>

362
00:28:05,013 --> 00:28:06,665
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

363
00:28:06,665 --> 00:28:08,600
This is insane.

364
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:10,143
<i>Okay.</i>

365
00:28:10,143 --> 00:28:13,446
<i>I'll take your luggage and get off.</i>

366
00:28:14,606 --> 00:28:16,320
<i>Thank you.</i>

367
00:28:18,151 --> 00:28:21,627
This guy is seriously unbelievable.

368
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:36,360
Fishing Cell!

369
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:37,799
You're heading home already?

370
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,549
Yeah, but I came up empty today.

371
00:28:40,549 --> 00:28:41,700
Why?

372
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:44,769
Yumi was pissed all day.

373
00:28:45,667 --> 00:28:47,414
You didn't catch a single angry snapper?

374
00:28:47,414 --> 00:28:49,958
There were tons of them.

375
00:28:49,958 --> 00:28:53,500
Seriously, so many today.

376
00:28:58,542 --> 00:29:02,176
<i>Looks like a full haul again!</i>

377
00:29:25,010 --> 00:29:26,975
Did they just get struck by lightning?

378
00:29:26,975 --> 00:29:28,958
Yeah, all of a sudden.

379
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:30,157
Hold on.

380
00:29:30,157 --> 00:29:33,228
If all the angry snappers are gone...

381
00:29:44,802 --> 00:29:48,281
That means Yumi's anger is gone.

382
00:29:48,281 --> 00:29:51,672
But she was clearly furious.

383
00:30:16,242 --> 00:30:19,336
The Hysterical Cell should be here...

384
00:30:20,655 --> 00:30:21,858
No.

385
00:30:21,858 --> 00:30:24,569
The Hysterical Cell is asleep.

386
00:30:24,569 --> 00:30:26,237
Then what is it?

387
00:30:26,237 --> 00:30:27,268
This is weird.

388
00:30:27,268 --> 00:30:30,533
We've never had lightning like that
in Yumi Village.

389
00:30:31,458 --> 00:30:32,490
Wait!

390
00:30:32,490 --> 00:30:34,442
Maybe as Yumi's getting older,

391
00:30:34,442 --> 00:30:37,346
she's developing some kind of
weird climate changes?

392
00:30:37,346 --> 00:30:38,813
Like...

393
00:30:38,813 --> 00:30:41,875
menopause symptoms?

394
00:30:41,875 --> 00:30:46,083
But there's no way
Yumi's at that stage already.

395
00:30:49,844 --> 00:30:51,797
What is it?

396
00:30:52,667 --> 00:30:54,833
Hey!

397
00:30:56,808 --> 00:30:58,640
What is it?

398
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:01,025
Come on, what?

399
00:31:26,025 --> 00:31:27,924
Power's back on.

400
00:31:29,429 --> 00:31:31,036
Let's get to work, Soon Rok.

401
00:31:31,036 --> 00:31:34,069
We've got a ton to do.

402
00:31:57,796 --> 00:32:00,005
<i>Writer Kim, I'm on the train.</i>

403
00:32:00,005 --> 00:32:03,158
<i>I'll be there in about 15 minutes.</i>

404
00:32:04,208 --> 00:32:07,415
<i>I'll be waiting at Platform 9.</i>

405
00:32:41,667 --> 00:32:44,333
How many minutes left?

406
00:32:44,333 --> 00:32:45,708
Five minutes.

407
00:32:45,708 --> 00:32:48,087
- Good.
- Okay.

408
00:32:48,087 --> 00:32:50,945
Five minutes till that asshole gets here.

409
00:32:50,945 --> 00:32:53,296
Let's not get dragged into his crap again.

410
00:32:53,296 --> 00:32:55,567
Smirking, stepping out to take calls...

411
00:32:55,567 --> 00:32:58,758
If he pulls any more bullshit
and skips the train again...

412
00:32:58,758 --> 00:33:00,958
we're not letting it slide.

413
00:33:00,958 --> 00:33:03,112
We crush him.

414
00:33:03,112 --> 00:33:05,646
We wreck him.

415
00:33:13,167 --> 00:33:14,922
How much time left?

416
00:33:14,922 --> 00:33:16,532
One minute.

417
00:33:16,532 --> 00:33:19,189
He's almost here.

418
00:33:19,189 --> 00:33:22,312
<i>The train is arriving now.</i>

419
00:33:24,288 --> 00:33:25,748
Finally!

420
00:33:25,748 --> 00:33:27,625
We crush him.

421
00:33:27,625 --> 00:33:30,118
Let's wreck him.

422
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:43,891
Where is that bastard?

423
00:33:43,891 --> 00:33:46,393
I don't see him.

424
00:33:46,393 --> 00:33:48,145
Did he bail again?

425
00:33:48,145 --> 00:33:51,114
If he bailed again, I swear...

426
00:33:56,545 --> 00:33:58,807
- There he is!
- There he is, that bastard!

427
00:33:58,807 --> 00:34:00,872
That annoying piece of...

428
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:03,520
What is it?

429
00:35:17,123 --> 00:35:19,068
I'm so sorry.

430
00:35:19,068 --> 00:35:21,320
That was a ridiculous mistake.

431
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:23,698
I got off for a second and missed it...

432
00:35:23,698 --> 00:35:25,658
I'm really sorry.

433
00:35:25,658 --> 00:35:27,410
Well... Okay.

434
00:35:27,410 --> 00:35:29,162
They said they'd send a car,

435
00:35:29,162 --> 00:35:31,372
but it hasn't arrived yet.

436
00:35:31,372 --> 00:35:34,083
Still, we should have enough time.

437
00:35:34,083 --> 00:35:35,168
That's a relief.

438
00:35:35,168 --> 00:35:37,712
We can head over now.

439
00:35:37,712 --> 00:35:39,755
And...

440
00:35:39,755 --> 00:35:41,340
about earlier,

441
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:43,926
I didn't answer you back then...

442
00:35:43,926 --> 00:35:45,928
It really was the schedule.

443
00:35:45,928 --> 00:35:48,181
There's no other reason.

444
00:35:48,181 --> 00:35:51,328
If I gave you the wrong impression, I'm sorry.

445
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:58,858
Look.

446
00:35:58,858 --> 00:36:01,360
Love Cell is gone.

447
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:03,446
Did it wake up?

448
00:36:03,446 --> 00:36:04,655
Why?

449
00:36:04,655 --> 00:36:05,823
I don't know.

450
00:36:05,823 --> 00:36:08,289
Where did it go?

451
00:36:09,698 --> 00:36:11,162
Wait.

452
00:36:11,162 --> 00:36:13,795
Then that lightning...

453
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:17,761
Let's go.

454
00:36:36,270 --> 00:36:37,338
Stuff like this...

455
00:36:37,338 --> 00:36:40,149
only happens in Yumi's novels.

456
00:36:40,149 --> 00:36:42,117
This is real?

457
00:36:44,517 --> 00:36:47,073
Can something just hit you like lightning...

458
00:36:47,073 --> 00:36:48,999
out of nowhere?

459
00:36:49,792 --> 00:36:53,667
[Episode 9: Drawing the Line
Between Work and Personal Life]

460
00:36:54,339 --> 00:36:56,125
Alright, now for today's featured work,

461
00:36:56,125 --> 00:37:00,059
please welcome the writer of
"The Scent of Sincerity," Kim Yumi.

462
00:37:00,059 --> 00:37:02,859
[Book Talk]

463
00:37:07,272 --> 00:37:10,833
Hi, hello. I'm writer Kim Yumi.

464
00:37:10,833 --> 00:37:14,158
Now we'll move on to the Q&A session.

465
00:37:14,158 --> 00:37:15,851
If anyone has questions for her...

466
00:37:15,851 --> 00:37:18,771
Honestly, becoming a writer

467
00:37:18,771 --> 00:37:24,219
was just a vague childhood dream of mine.

468
00:37:24,219 --> 00:37:26,304
As I got older...

469
00:37:26,304 --> 00:37:29,282
It was short, but I had a wonderful time.

470
00:37:29,282 --> 00:37:33,931
I'll be back with another great piece soon.
Thank you.

471
00:37:35,726 --> 00:37:37,375
I'm a huge fan.

472
00:37:37,375 --> 00:37:39,750
Oh, thank you.

473
00:37:40,651 --> 00:37:43,195
Smile.

474
00:37:43,963 --> 00:37:46,261
- What's your name?
- Jin Hee Jung.

475
00:37:46,261 --> 00:37:48,235
Jin Hee Jung.

476
00:37:50,396 --> 00:37:53,183
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

477
00:38:02,690 --> 00:38:05,921
All her photos turned out great.

478
00:38:05,921 --> 00:38:09,636
Oh, she even got flowers.

479
00:38:09,636 --> 00:38:12,840
She's basically a superstar now.

480
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,749
So pretty.

481
00:38:14,749 --> 00:38:16,553
Here's your cake.

482
00:38:16,553 --> 00:38:18,217
Okay.

483
00:38:20,374 --> 00:38:22,899
- Thank you.
- Bye.

484
00:38:34,292 --> 00:38:37,783
Writer Kim, I'm here.

485
00:38:37,783 --> 00:38:39,593
Oh, you're here.

486
00:38:40,463 --> 00:38:43,215
How was Busan?

487
00:38:44,056 --> 00:38:46,642
Yeah... it was good.

488
00:38:46,642 --> 00:38:49,188
I saw photos from your book event online.

489
00:38:49,188 --> 00:38:51,440
There were a lot of people.

490
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:54,200
Yeah, more than I expected.

491
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:57,599
You've got tons of fans.

492
00:38:57,599 --> 00:38:59,090
Not really.

493
00:38:59,090 --> 00:39:02,400
There were several guest authors.

494
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:03,802
But still...

495
00:39:03,802 --> 00:39:06,771
You seem really calm today.

496
00:39:08,125 --> 00:39:09,174
Me?

497
00:39:09,174 --> 00:39:12,961
Yeah, unusually calm.

498
00:39:12,961 --> 00:39:15,353
Nothing to get worked up about.

499
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:17,535
Same as always.

500
00:39:17,535 --> 00:39:19,055
Yeah?

501
00:39:23,744 --> 00:39:26,389
Calm, my ass.

502
00:39:26,389 --> 00:39:28,322
She just doesn't know it yet.

503
00:39:28,322 --> 00:39:29,500
The whole place

504
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:32,917
is in complete chaos right now!

505
00:39:38,237 --> 00:39:42,115
Just look at the state of things
these past few days.

506
00:39:42,115 --> 00:39:43,919
Still, she can't show it.

507
00:39:43,919 --> 00:39:47,430
If she looks calm, that's a win.

508
00:39:48,284 --> 00:39:50,784
Should we go to the hospital?

509
00:39:52,844 --> 00:39:54,312
After that lightning strike,

510
00:39:54,312 --> 00:39:57,715
she's showing signs of partial memory loss.

511
00:39:57,715 --> 00:40:00,833
"Partial memory loss?"

512
00:40:00,833 --> 00:40:04,050
When he took off his glasses
and let his hair down...

513
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:07,625
he looked like a puppy.

514
00:40:07,625 --> 00:40:11,747
And when he smiled...

515
00:40:11,747 --> 00:40:13,398
So cute.

516
00:40:13,398 --> 00:40:16,042
- Right, totally.
- Right.

517
00:40:16,042 --> 00:40:17,104
Huh?

518
00:40:17,104 --> 00:40:20,436
Weren't you all furious at Soon Rok?

519
00:40:20,436 --> 00:40:22,217
Don't you remember?

520
00:40:23,549 --> 00:40:24,707
Were we?

521
00:40:24,707 --> 00:40:26,845
Wait, yeah... I think we were mad.

522
00:40:26,845 --> 00:40:30,036
But why were we mad again?

523
00:40:30,036 --> 00:40:32,207
Because

524
00:40:32,207 --> 00:40:35,167
he said he was leaving?

525
00:40:35,167 --> 00:40:37,055
- Oh... right.
- Oh... right.

526
00:40:37,055 --> 00:40:39,898
- That must be it.
- That must be it.

527
00:40:44,667 --> 00:40:47,750
Love Cell is gone.

528
00:40:49,193 --> 00:40:51,745
And Naughty Cell...

529
00:40:52,379 --> 00:40:54,797
The guy scouts...

530
00:40:54,797 --> 00:40:57,564
Tongue Cell is gone too.

531
00:40:58,281 --> 00:41:00,042
Why are Naughty Cell and Tongue Cell awake?

532
00:41:00,042 --> 00:41:01,945
She doesn't even have a boyfriend.

533
00:41:01,945 --> 00:41:03,708
What are they even going to do?

534
00:41:03,708 --> 00:41:05,869
They've got nothing to do anyway!

535
00:41:05,869 --> 00:41:07,792
That lightning just triggered them.

536
00:41:07,792 --> 00:41:10,999
They didn't wake up for a reason.

537
00:41:10,999 --> 00:41:12,667
Find them. All of them.

538
00:41:12,667 --> 00:41:14,708
Before they cause trouble again!

539
00:41:14,708 --> 00:41:16,500
Without them, I was...

540
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:20,833
I mean, Yumi was perfectly fine.

541
00:41:23,749 --> 00:41:25,568
It's just a glitch from the lightning.

542
00:41:25,568 --> 00:41:27,326
Nothing serious.

543
00:41:27,326 --> 00:41:29,458
Everything will go back to normal soon.

544
00:41:29,458 --> 00:41:32,009
She won't even see Soon Rok again anyway.

545
00:41:32,009 --> 00:41:34,275
Right.

546
00:41:35,625 --> 00:41:39,667
Give it a few days,
and it'll be like nothing ever happened.

547
00:41:46,064 --> 00:41:47,675
Let's start the meeting.

548
00:41:48,794 --> 00:41:50,508
What's this? A cake?

549
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:52,172
Yes, it's a birthday cake.

550
00:41:52,172 --> 00:41:53,448
A birthday cake?

551
00:41:53,448 --> 00:41:57,519
I didn't know, but today's PD Shin's birthday.

552
00:41:57,519 --> 00:42:01,283
I set up a messenger alert,
and it popped up this morning.

553
00:42:01,283 --> 00:42:04,253
Since we had a meeting today, perfect timing.

554
00:42:05,184 --> 00:42:06,208
Isn't it pretty?

555
00:42:06,208 --> 00:42:08,553
It's a low-sugar cake.

556
00:42:08,553 --> 00:42:10,607
I guess I didn't tell you.

557
00:42:10,607 --> 00:42:12,937
He's not coming today.

558
00:42:12,937 --> 00:42:14,631
- Why not?
- Starting today,

559
00:42:14,631 --> 00:42:16,566
he's off our team.

560
00:42:16,566 --> 00:42:18,818
- What?
- Last week was his last.

561
00:42:18,818 --> 00:42:20,737
I forgot to tell you.

562
00:42:20,737 --> 00:42:22,447
Why?

563
00:42:22,447 --> 00:42:25,658
He's handling too many teams.
His schedule got messy.

564
00:42:25,658 --> 00:42:28,995
Let's just eat the cake ourselves.
It looks good.

565
00:42:28,995 --> 00:42:32,457
I'm so bummed. Seriously bummed.

566
00:42:32,457 --> 00:42:34,876
Come on, that's a bit much.

567
00:42:34,876 --> 00:42:36,711
I liked PD Shin.

568
00:42:36,711 --> 00:42:39,797
Did you come to this meeting
for personal reasons?

569
00:42:39,797 --> 00:42:41,667
Aren't we doing a farewell?

570
00:42:41,667 --> 00:42:43,076
At least let's have a team dinner.

571
00:42:43,076 --> 00:42:46,079
A farewell? We barely even worked together.

572
00:42:46,079 --> 00:42:47,764
But it's his birthday.

573
00:42:47,764 --> 00:42:50,183
Let's do a farewell slash birthday party.

574
00:42:50,183 --> 00:42:53,127
He's not coming here anymore.

575
00:42:55,375 --> 00:42:58,816
If you're that disappointed,
celebrate with him on your own.

576
00:42:58,816 --> 00:43:01,525
Okay, I will.

577
00:43:06,950 --> 00:43:08,910
I sent him a message.

578
00:43:08,910 --> 00:43:10,495
Saying happy birthday?

579
00:43:10,495 --> 00:43:14,374
I said I'm really sad he left so suddenly.

580
00:43:14,374 --> 00:43:17,652
I had no idea you liked him that much.

581
00:43:17,652 --> 00:43:19,525
He was low-key cute.

582
00:43:19,525 --> 00:43:23,956
Especially without his glasses,
he looked like a puppy.

583
00:43:23,956 --> 00:43:27,494
He took them off once...

584
00:43:28,179 --> 00:43:30,348
and he was seriously adorable.

585
00:43:30,348 --> 00:43:33,251
So I told him not to wear glasses,
try contacts instead.

586
00:43:33,251 --> 00:43:35,871
And you know what he said?

587
00:43:37,146 --> 00:43:39,384
What?

588
00:43:41,542 --> 00:43:44,279
<i>I wear them to look cold.</i>

589
00:43:44,279 --> 00:43:46,364
What does that even mean?

590
00:43:46,364 --> 00:43:48,973
He wants to seem distant

591
00:43:48,973 --> 00:43:51,875
so people won't bother him.

592
00:43:51,875 --> 00:43:53,854
That's cute and funny at the same time, right?

593
00:43:53,854 --> 00:43:55,614
[PD Shin Soon Rok]

594
00:43:55,614 --> 00:43:58,357
It's PD Shin.

595
00:43:58,357 --> 00:44:00,175
Oh, Hello?

596
00:44:00,175 --> 00:44:02,523
Hi.

597
00:44:02,523 --> 00:44:07,135
Yeah, I'm at the meeting right now.
I heard from Writer Kim.

598
00:44:07,135 --> 00:44:09,370
Yes, at her studio.

599
00:44:09,370 --> 00:44:11,083
Really?

600
00:44:11,083 --> 00:44:13,374
Okay, got it.

601
00:44:13,374 --> 00:44:15,401
Okay.

602
00:44:17,524 --> 00:44:20,546
He's nearby right now.

603
00:44:20,546 --> 00:44:21,688
Oh, really?

604
00:44:21,688 --> 00:44:22,940
He said he might stop by.

605
00:44:22,940 --> 00:44:23,971
Right now?

606
00:44:23,971 --> 00:44:25,847
- Here?
- Yes.

607
00:44:25,847 --> 00:44:29,118
He asked if it's okay to come up,
so I said yes.

608
00:44:29,118 --> 00:44:33,453
Perfect timing.
We can cut the cake when he gets here.

609
00:44:33,453 --> 00:44:35,654
Let's surprise him.

610
00:44:38,083 --> 00:44:39,126
What?

611
00:44:39,126 --> 00:44:40,611
Things were finally settling down...

612
00:44:40,611 --> 00:44:43,817
why is he coming back now?

613
00:44:43,817 --> 00:44:45,950
What's that sound?

614
00:44:55,042 --> 00:44:56,684
Hey, Thump, Boom!

615
00:44:56,684 --> 00:44:59,570
Why are you banging the drums?

616
00:45:02,417 --> 00:45:05,573
Why is the heart racing all of a sudden?

617
00:45:05,573 --> 00:45:08,196
I'll leave this in the room
and bring it out later.

618
00:45:08,196 --> 00:45:09,591
Okay.

619
00:45:20,165 --> 00:45:22,460
What a ridiculous guy.

620
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:25,435
He just left on his own,
and he's suddenly showing up again?

621
00:45:37,898 --> 00:45:39,887
He's here.

622
00:45:41,587 --> 00:45:42,825
Oh, Writer Kim.

623
00:45:42,825 --> 00:45:45,411
Can I use it just once?

624
00:45:45,411 --> 00:45:46,458
Use what?

625
00:45:46,458 --> 00:45:49,468
Your lip gloss. I forgot to bring mine.

626
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:53,307
Aren't you already wearing some?

627
00:45:56,786 --> 00:45:59,472
My lips keep getting chapped.

628
00:46:07,672 --> 00:46:10,683
Nice. I like that it has color.

629
00:46:15,917 --> 00:46:19,307
Why are you putting on lip gloss
all of a sudden?

630
00:46:19,307 --> 00:46:22,143
I told you already.

631
00:46:22,143 --> 00:46:24,920
My lips are chapped.

632
00:46:25,563 --> 00:46:27,982
- Hello.
- Hello.

633
00:46:27,982 --> 00:46:30,829
PD Shin is here.

634
00:46:49,754 --> 00:46:50,796
<i>What?</i>

635
00:46:50,796 --> 00:46:52,131
<i>Why is my heart racing?</i>

636
00:46:52,131 --> 00:46:53,417
<i>What's wrong...</i>

637
00:46:53,417 --> 00:46:55,880
<i>What's wrong with it this time?</i>

638
00:46:58,971 --> 00:47:01,418
Hello, Writer Kim.

639
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:09,371
You're here.

640
00:47:13,903 --> 00:47:14,987
Did you get some rest?

641
00:47:14,987 --> 00:47:16,222
After Busan?

642
00:47:16,222 --> 00:47:17,528
Well... yeah.

643
00:47:17,528 --> 00:47:18,679
But what brings you...

644
00:47:18,679 --> 00:47:20,910
I had something to take care of nearby.

645
00:47:20,910 --> 00:47:22,828
I was going to stop by anyway,

646
00:47:22,828 --> 00:47:25,414
and then Na Hui contacted me.

647
00:47:25,414 --> 00:47:27,299
I see.

648
00:47:27,299 --> 00:47:29,872
This is for you.

649
00:47:29,872 --> 00:47:31,195
What is it?

650
00:47:31,195 --> 00:47:32,989
The event organizers

651
00:47:32,989 --> 00:47:35,508
sent over high-res photos
from your book concert.

652
00:47:35,508 --> 00:47:38,541
So I picked a good one and framed it.

653
00:47:39,345 --> 00:47:41,646
You look great in it.

654
00:47:43,808 --> 00:47:46,978
You didn't have to go this far...

655
00:47:46,978 --> 00:47:48,862
Thank you.

656
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:55,653
Happy birthday, PD Shin.

657
00:47:55,653 --> 00:47:58,072
It's your birthday today, right?

658
00:47:58,072 --> 00:47:59,223
How did you know...

659
00:47:59,223 --> 00:48:01,117
I just know these things.

660
00:48:01,117 --> 00:48:03,160
How did you find out?

661
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:05,621
She's quick with stuff like that.

662
00:48:05,621 --> 00:48:07,356
Okay, let's sing.

663
00:48:07,356 --> 00:48:08,791
No, that's okay.

664
00:48:08,791 --> 00:48:10,459
Writer Kim, let's sing.

665
00:48:10,459 --> 00:48:13,875
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

666
00:48:13,875 --> 00:48:16,365
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

667
00:48:16,365 --> 00:48:18,000
<i>Wait.</i>

668
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,843
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

669
00:48:19,843 --> 00:48:23,121
Next comes "dear..."

670
00:48:23,121 --> 00:48:24,333
Should we use this word?

671
00:48:24,333 --> 00:48:27,017
It's just part of the song, even for enemies.

672
00:48:27,017 --> 00:48:28,727
What's the problem with that?

673
00:48:28,727 --> 00:48:30,729
But still...

674
00:48:30,729 --> 00:48:33,215
To Shin Soon Rok?

675
00:48:34,233 --> 00:48:37,803
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

676
00:48:37,803 --> 00:48:39,738
<i>♪ Dear... ♪</i>

677
00:48:39,738 --> 00:48:41,990
<i>♪ PD Shin ♪</i>

678
00:48:41,990 --> 00:48:46,537
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

679
00:48:46,537 --> 00:48:48,852
<i>Did Yumi just blush?</i>

680
00:48:48,852 --> 00:48:51,124
<i>Why?</i>

681
00:48:51,124 --> 00:48:52,334
Put it out.

682
00:48:52,334 --> 00:48:53,660
Okay.

683
00:48:56,459 --> 00:48:58,006
Congratulations.

684
00:48:58,006 --> 00:49:00,232
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

685
00:49:00,939 --> 00:49:03,303
This is a bit overwhelming.

686
00:49:03,303 --> 00:49:05,013
The cake...

687
00:49:05,013 --> 00:49:07,140
Please have some before you go.

688
00:49:07,140 --> 00:49:08,976
Here, have a seat.

689
00:49:08,976 --> 00:49:10,909
Yeah.

690
00:49:10,909 --> 00:49:12,479
I'll do it.

691
00:49:12,479 --> 00:49:14,815
No, I'll bring it. You cut the cake.

692
00:49:14,815 --> 00:49:16,647
Okay.

693
00:49:23,156 --> 00:49:25,225
I got the candles right, didn't I?

694
00:49:25,225 --> 00:49:26,697
Your 30th birthday.

695
00:49:26,697 --> 00:49:30,482
<i>What? He is only 30?</i>

696
00:49:30,482 --> 00:49:32,700
No, I'm not 30.

697
00:49:32,700 --> 00:49:33,911
<i>Right.</i>

698
00:49:33,911 --> 00:49:36,171
<i>He must be around my age.</i>

699
00:49:36,171 --> 00:49:37,311
Exactly...

700
00:49:37,311 --> 00:49:39,228
I'm 29.

701
00:49:40,344 --> 00:49:41,758
Seriously?

702
00:49:41,758 --> 00:49:44,333
Then we're only a year apart?

703
00:49:44,333 --> 00:49:45,924
Yes.

704
00:49:45,924 --> 00:49:49,688
<i>What? He's in his twenties?</i>

705
00:49:49,688 --> 00:49:53,895
Then how old is he compared to Yumi?

706
00:49:53,895 --> 00:49:55,528
One, two...

707
00:49:55,528 --> 00:49:58,721
Why are you even counting?

708
00:49:58,721 --> 00:50:00,419
What are you going to do with that?

709
00:50:00,419 --> 00:50:02,762
It hurts.

710
00:50:05,641 --> 00:50:07,757
I'm getting coffee.

711
00:50:07,757 --> 00:50:09,328
Anyone want some?

712
00:50:09,328 --> 00:50:12,079
Can I have an iced Americano?

713
00:50:12,079 --> 00:50:13,498
- Of course.
- Thank you.

714
00:50:13,498 --> 00:50:14,524
I'll get it.

715
00:50:14,524 --> 00:50:16,343
I'll do it. Want an Americano too?

716
00:50:16,343 --> 00:50:17,821
Yes, please.

717
00:50:19,596 --> 00:50:22,333
Did you have seaweed soup today?

718
00:50:22,333 --> 00:50:23,383
No.

719
00:50:23,383 --> 00:50:25,843
Why not? Do you live alone?

720
00:50:25,843 --> 00:50:26,911
Yes.

721
00:50:26,911 --> 00:50:28,888
I moved out in college.

722
00:50:28,888 --> 00:50:31,015
<i>He lives alone?</i>

723
00:50:31,015 --> 00:50:32,166
Then your parents?

724
00:50:32,166 --> 00:50:34,794
They retired

725
00:50:34,794 --> 00:50:38,345
and moved to a country house in Yangpyeong.

726
00:50:38,345 --> 00:50:40,358
Then do you visit every weekend?

727
00:50:40,358 --> 00:50:41,647
Sometimes.

728
00:50:41,647 --> 00:50:44,092
I usually just rest at home on weekends.

729
00:50:44,092 --> 00:50:46,364
So you're a homebody.

730
00:50:46,364 --> 00:50:49,104
A committed homebody.

731
00:50:51,035 --> 00:50:52,912
<i>Is he a homebody too?</i>

732
00:50:52,912 --> 00:50:54,355
<i>Same as me.</i>

733
00:50:54,355 --> 00:50:56,457
What are you doing for your birthday?

734
00:50:56,457 --> 00:50:57,905
<i>A date?</i>

735
00:51:00,388 --> 00:51:03,267
With who?

736
00:51:03,267 --> 00:51:04,543
Nice question.

737
00:51:04,543 --> 00:51:07,965
He doesn't have a girlfriend.

738
00:51:07,965 --> 00:51:10,060
So what?

739
00:51:14,715 --> 00:51:15,917
Here.

740
00:51:15,917 --> 00:51:18,077
Thank you.

741
00:51:19,162 --> 00:51:21,075
I'll enjoy it.

742
00:51:29,678 --> 00:51:32,287
The coffee's good.

743
00:51:32,287 --> 00:51:33,886
Nice and smooth, right?

744
00:51:33,886 --> 00:51:36,237
Yeah, and the cake's good too.

745
00:51:36,237 --> 00:51:38,142
Thanks.

746
00:51:38,142 --> 00:51:41,914
I didn't buy it. Na Hui did.

747
00:51:41,914 --> 00:51:43,469
I bought it.

748
00:51:43,469 --> 00:51:45,446
The cake's really good.

749
00:51:45,446 --> 00:51:46,757
By the way,

750
00:51:46,757 --> 00:51:50,790
I think this is the most
I've ever heard you talk.

751
00:51:52,083 --> 00:51:54,732
- Yeah?
- You think so too, right?

752
00:51:54,732 --> 00:51:56,759
Yeah.

753
00:51:57,460 --> 00:51:59,414
Maybe because I'm not here for work.

754
00:51:59,414 --> 00:52:01,271
I feel more relaxed.

755
00:52:01,271 --> 00:52:04,358
So you felt uncomfortable coming here before?

756
00:52:04,358 --> 00:52:05,609
I just...

757
00:52:05,609 --> 00:52:08,220
tend to separate work
and personal life too strictly.

758
00:52:08,220 --> 00:52:12,313
It just happens without me realizing.

759
00:52:12,958 --> 00:52:14,643
Not the best trait.

760
00:52:14,643 --> 00:52:17,208
Then come by casually sometime.

761
00:52:17,208 --> 00:52:18,343
I will.

762
00:52:18,343 --> 00:52:20,415
So what are you doing tonight?

763
00:52:20,415 --> 00:52:21,817
Since no date?

764
00:52:21,817 --> 00:52:23,001
I'm heading to Busan.

765
00:52:23,001 --> 00:52:24,169
Again?

766
00:52:24,169 --> 00:52:26,338
We have a publishing workshop.

767
00:52:26,338 --> 00:52:29,007
Three nights, four days. All the writers too.

768
00:52:29,007 --> 00:52:30,659
I heard you're not going

769
00:52:30,659 --> 00:52:33,220
since it overlaps with your Busan trip.

770
00:52:33,220 --> 00:52:36,056
Yeah, that's right.

771
00:52:36,056 --> 00:52:38,092
It felt like too much to go again so soon.

772
00:52:38,092 --> 00:52:41,685
But I ended up having to go anyway.

773
00:52:43,392 --> 00:52:46,585
That must be tough,
especially on your birthday.

774
00:52:48,860 --> 00:52:51,250
I should get going now.

775
00:52:51,250 --> 00:52:54,708
Happy birthday again.

776
00:52:54,708 --> 00:52:56,616
Thank you.

777
00:53:04,295 --> 00:53:05,460
Bye.

778
00:53:05,460 --> 00:53:07,077
Have a good day.

779
00:53:11,274 --> 00:53:13,426
Why did I say I wasn't going to the workshop?

780
00:53:13,426 --> 00:53:14,511
Everyone else is going.

781
00:53:14,511 --> 00:53:15,667
- Hey.
- Yeah?

782
00:53:15,667 --> 00:53:19,099
I barely have time to write.
I can't waste a whole week in Busan.

783
00:53:19,099 --> 00:53:21,548
But Soon Rok's going...

784
00:53:21,548 --> 00:53:22,906
So?

785
00:53:22,906 --> 00:53:25,981
- Nothing.
- Hey, what's wrong with you too?

786
00:53:25,981 --> 00:53:28,500
You're the Rational Cell. Get a grip!

787
00:53:28,500 --> 00:53:31,250
Going to the workshop isn't bad
for work either.

788
00:53:31,250 --> 00:53:33,323
It is.

789
00:53:33,323 --> 00:53:35,586
It is!

790
00:53:35,586 --> 00:53:37,311
Especially now!

791
00:53:37,311 --> 00:53:39,739
More than ever!

792
00:53:41,036 --> 00:53:44,455
Let's just focus and write.

793
00:53:46,627 --> 00:53:49,321
So what if she steps out briefly
to take out the trash...

794
00:53:49,321 --> 00:53:51,473
and the Maltese disappears?

795
00:53:51,473 --> 00:53:55,211
It slips out through the open door,
gets on the elevator, and vanishes...

796
00:53:55,211 --> 00:53:58,911
The male lead finds out
and gets really mad at her...

797
00:54:01,157 --> 00:54:03,667
That's a good idea too.

798
00:54:03,667 --> 00:54:06,667
Or what if the Maltese turns out to be sick,

799
00:54:06,667 --> 00:54:08,565
so she takes it to the vet

800
00:54:08,565 --> 00:54:11,665
but her phone dies...

801
00:54:14,756 --> 00:54:16,127
Looking for the Maltese...

802
00:54:16,127 --> 00:54:18,367
That's...

803
00:54:18,367 --> 00:54:20,891
good too.

804
00:54:20,891 --> 00:54:22,647
But Na Hui...

805
00:54:22,647 --> 00:54:23,787
Yes?

806
00:54:23,787 --> 00:54:27,041
Should we wrap up early today?

807
00:54:27,041 --> 00:54:28,209
Sorry?

808
00:54:28,209 --> 00:54:31,504
I've got something to take care of.

809
00:54:31,504 --> 00:54:34,156
Let's keep it short today
and continue online tomorrow.

810
00:54:34,156 --> 00:54:37,384
Your idea is good.
I think we can wrap it up quickly.

811
00:54:37,384 --> 00:54:39,294
Okay.

812
00:54:39,294 --> 00:54:41,694
You're an idea bank.

813
00:54:44,032 --> 00:54:45,434
What's going on?

814
00:54:45,434 --> 00:54:47,019
What now?

815
00:54:47,019 --> 00:54:49,880
We've barely been in this meeting!

816
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:52,281
Still don't get it?

817
00:54:56,153 --> 00:54:57,988
You really don't know

818
00:54:57,988 --> 00:54:59,557
why Yumi's acting like this?

819
00:54:59,557 --> 00:55:01,835
Oh, Love Cell!

820
00:55:01,835 --> 00:55:03,754
Where did you go?

821
00:55:03,754 --> 00:55:05,287
Hey, Love Cell is here!

822
00:55:05,287 --> 00:55:07,522
- Get her!
- Got it!

823
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:15,292
Idiots!

824
00:55:15,292 --> 00:55:16,949
How can someone in love

825
00:55:16,949 --> 00:55:19,842
possibly stay calm?

826
00:55:19,842 --> 00:55:21,333
What are you talking about?

827
00:55:21,333 --> 00:55:23,639
The world has changed.

828
00:55:23,639 --> 00:55:25,266
The moment that lightning struck,

829
00:55:25,266 --> 00:55:27,502
Yumi changed.

830
00:55:30,813 --> 00:55:33,148
<i>Hello, Writer Kim?</i>

831
00:55:33,148 --> 00:55:35,025
PD Jang.

832
00:55:35,025 --> 00:55:36,860
Are you in Busan?

833
00:55:36,860 --> 00:55:40,393
Yeah, I came down this morning with the editor.

834
00:55:41,198 --> 00:55:44,018
I'm thinking of coming down too.

835
00:55:44,018 --> 00:55:46,078
Would there be a place for me to stay?

836
00:55:46,078 --> 00:55:48,125
Oh, you're coming?

837
00:55:48,125 --> 00:55:52,542
Yes. It's rare to see all the writers together,

838
00:55:52,542 --> 00:55:55,253
so I thought I should go.

839
00:55:55,253 --> 00:55:57,292
Of course, you're more than welcome.

840
00:55:57,292 --> 00:55:59,340
Come on down.

841
00:55:59,340 --> 00:56:02,051
I'll take the evening train.

842
00:56:02,051 --> 00:56:04,736
<i>The editor will be glad to hear that.</i>

843
00:56:04,736 --> 00:56:05,999
<i>Come down soon.</i>

844
00:56:05,999 --> 00:56:08,424
I'll call you when I get there.

845
00:56:08,424 --> 00:56:10,436
<i>Okay.</i>

846
00:56:11,917 --> 00:56:15,208
I've lost it. I've seriously lost it.

847
00:56:18,167 --> 00:56:20,277
Now, the Prime Cell position...

848
00:56:20,277 --> 00:56:21,945
- I'm taking it back.
- What?

849
00:56:21,945 --> 00:56:25,240
You might as well hand over this place too.

850
00:56:25,240 --> 00:56:26,909
Are you insane?

851
00:56:26,909 --> 00:56:28,994
Who do you think you are, taking Prime Cell?

852
00:56:28,994 --> 00:56:32,230
What are you doing? Get her!

853
00:57:10,208 --> 00:57:12,663
What the hell are you doing, Kim Yumi?

854
00:57:12,663 --> 00:57:13,997
Seriously...

855
00:57:13,997 --> 00:57:18,570
What are you doing? You've completely lost it.

856
00:57:25,509 --> 00:57:27,261
You've lost it.

857
00:57:27,261 --> 00:57:29,513
You can't even separate work and personal life.

858
00:57:29,513 --> 00:57:32,933
And someone out there is
so perfectly professional...

859
00:57:32,933 --> 00:57:35,433
You've seriously lost it.

860
00:57:59,293 --> 00:58:02,093
[Seoul]

861
00:58:04,564 --> 00:58:07,176
God, how old are you, seriously?

862
00:58:07,176 --> 00:58:09,280
What the hell is wrong with you...

863
00:58:09,280 --> 00:58:10,888
Sorry?

864
00:58:10,888 --> 00:58:13,201
Oh, nothing.

865
00:58:13,855 --> 00:58:16,407
I've seriously lost it.

866
00:58:25,736 --> 00:58:27,302
Hello, PD Jang.

867
00:58:27,302 --> 00:58:30,491
You haven't gotten on the train yet, right?

868
00:58:30,491 --> 00:58:32,632
I just got to the station.

869
00:58:32,632 --> 00:58:34,912
- I was about to buy a ticket...
<i>- Oh, perfect.</i>

870
00:58:34,912 --> 00:58:39,000
PD Shin is heading down now.
He's still at the station.

871
00:58:39,000 --> 00:58:40,083
Sorry?

872
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:42,361
<i>You can just come down with him.</i>

873
00:58:42,361 --> 00:58:45,005
<i>I'll have him buy your ticket.</i>

874
00:58:45,005 --> 00:58:47,156
Okay.

875
00:59:01,855 --> 00:59:03,607
This is insane.

876
00:59:03,607 --> 00:59:07,493
Why am I this nervous?
It's not even a big deal...

877
00:59:10,447 --> 00:59:12,520
Writer Kim.

878
00:59:47,867 --> 00:59:52,323
[A one-sided love has begun]

879
00:59:58,487 --> 00:59:59,500
<i>Fine.</i>

880
00:59:59,500 --> 01:00:01,714
<i>I'll admit it.</i>

881
01:00:01,714 --> 01:00:03,834
<i>I...</i>

882
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:05,419
<i>like</i>

883
01:00:05,419 --> 01:00:07,761
<i>Soon Rok.</i>

884
01:00:12,299 --> 01:00:15,236
You think you can take my place?

885
01:00:15,236 --> 01:00:17,513
I've built this up for years!

886
01:00:17,513 --> 01:00:20,814
I'm still the Prime Cell!

887
01:00:22,875 --> 01:00:23,936
Let's see, then.

888
01:00:23,936 --> 01:00:26,896
Who ends up winning.

889
01:00:26,896 --> 01:00:28,342
Ridiculous.

890
01:00:28,342 --> 01:00:31,417
Shin Soon Rok isn't even interested in Yumi.

891
01:00:31,417 --> 01:00:33,853
He doesn't even like her.

892
01:00:33,853 --> 01:00:34,988
She probably scares him.

893
01:00:34,988 --> 01:00:36,906
After the way she snapped at him.

894
01:00:36,906 --> 01:00:39,670
He's only dealing with her because it's work.

895
01:00:39,670 --> 01:00:42,166
Don't you get that?

896
01:00:50,319 --> 01:00:51,512
Have a seat.

897
01:00:51,512 --> 01:00:53,025
Okay.

898
01:01:02,413 --> 01:01:04,613
I thought you said you weren't going earlier.

899
01:01:04,613 --> 01:01:06,420
Yeah, I did...

900
01:01:06,420 --> 01:01:08,706
but the meeting wrapped up quickly.

901
01:01:08,706 --> 01:01:11,775
PD Jang kept insisting I come.

902
01:01:11,775 --> 01:01:13,928
I see.

903
01:01:13,928 --> 01:01:15,719
Guess we ended up going together.

904
01:01:15,719 --> 01:01:17,846
<i>The train is departing.</i>

905
01:01:17,846 --> 01:01:19,879
Yeah.

906
01:01:41,655 --> 01:01:43,807
Want me to grab you a coffee?

907
01:01:43,807 --> 01:01:46,226
I'm good. I already had one.

908
01:01:46,226 --> 01:01:48,319
Okay.

909
01:02:41,125 --> 01:02:42,574
See?

910
01:02:42,574 --> 01:02:45,035
You're really going to go for a hopeless crush?

911
01:02:45,035 --> 01:02:46,280
I don't care.

912
01:02:46,280 --> 01:02:47,563
What?

913
01:02:47,563 --> 01:02:49,622
What matters is...

914
01:02:49,622 --> 01:02:52,123
I'm awake now.

915
01:03:05,039 --> 01:03:06,681
What matters is...

916
01:03:06,681 --> 01:03:08,708
Yumi's dull, lifeless routine

917
01:03:08,708 --> 01:03:11,286
is finally over.

918
01:03:58,375 --> 01:03:59,400
<i>It's Soon Rok!</i>

919
01:03:59,400 --> 01:04:01,458
<i>This is insane, seriously!</i>

920
01:04:01,458 --> 01:04:03,071
<i>Yumi, get it together!</i>

921
01:04:03,071 --> 01:04:04,375
<i>This is writer Kim Ju Ho.</i>

922
01:04:04,375 --> 01:04:05,911
<i>Nice to meet you.</i>

923
01:04:05,911 --> 01:04:07,375
<i>If you don't mind me asking,
what year were you?</i>

924
01:04:07,375 --> 01:04:10,428
<i>Wait, wait! Why bring that up out of nowhere?</i>

925
01:04:10,428 --> 01:04:12,622
<i>You sure Yumi's single?</i>

926
01:04:12,622 --> 01:04:15,208
<i>Are they trying to
set me up with him or something?</i>

927
01:04:15,208 --> 01:04:17,293
<i>They actually look pretty good together, huh?</i>

928
01:04:17,293 --> 01:04:18,820
<i>I don't think so.</i>

929
01:04:18,820 --> 01:04:19,879
<i>Have some confidence.</i>

930
01:04:19,879 --> 01:04:21,464
<i>Let's make this a thing.</i>

931
01:04:21,464 --> 01:04:24,748
<i>- Let's make this a thing!
- Let's make this a thing!</i>
